HEADWORD: finger paint
<hw>finger paint</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A type of paint having the consistency of a thin paste or jelly,
which is applied to a surface by dipping fingers into the paint and
smearing the paint on the surface, usually in artistic patterns. It is
used primarily by children.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

